Payoneer is a financial services company that provides online money transfer and digital payment services. Payoneer account holders can send and receive funds into their bank account, Payoneer e-wallet, or onto a re-loadable prepaid MasterCard debit card that can be used online or at points-of-sale. The company specializes in facilitating cross-border B2B payments.
Payoneer has roughly four million users in more than 200 countries and territories, and provides cross-border transactions in more than 150 local currencies utilizing its banking network around the world to make local bank transfers.
Companies like Airbnb, Amazon, Google and Upwork use Payoneer to send mass payouts around the world. Payoneer is also used by eCommerce marketplaces worldwide such as Wish, Lazada, Shopee, Cdiscount, Newegg and Tophatter. They work with a wide variety of ad networks, to connect these firms with their network of publishers based outside of their headquartered country. Examples of firms they work with in this area include CJ Affiliate, Tradedoubler and ShareASale.
In the content creation space, Payoneer works with a variety of companies including GettyImages, Shutterstock, Pond5, 99designs, Stocky, Dreamstime Microstock, 123RF.com and DailyMotion, and a variety of freelance marketplaces such as Upwork, Fiverr, PeoplePerHour, One Hour Translation and Envato. Payoneer is also used by vacation rental sites like Airbnb, HomeAway and Pandabed.
Payoneer is a registered Member Service Provider (MSP) of MasterCard Incorporated. The company is headquartered in New York City.
